Summary

marketing contract hardening and runtime repair day

Today was split between making the marketing generation path more evidence-bound and repairing the coding-result return path so terminal state handling stayed truthful. The work did not add a new flagship surface. It tightened the rules around what the marketing system can claim, how generated artifacts are recorded, and how the worker reports completion back into the rest of the system.

The underlying pattern was consistent across both threads: reduce ambiguity, keep provenance visible, and stop the repo from implying more certainty than the runtime or source material actually support. That showed up in the marketing evidence ledger, the beta release sentinel, the generated campaign bundle, and the return-state repair in Guardian.

