- Reverted unintended frontend and campaign file carryover so the day’s work stayed bounded to the actual intended slices.

Important outcome

The main shift today is that both the marketing system and the coding-result path became more truthful about their own outputs.

The marketing side is no longer just producing copy. It is producing copy with a ledger, eligibility rules, run metadata, and archived artifacts that make the evidence path visible. That matters because the system can now say less when the source material is weaker, which is the correct direction for a repo that cares about claims staying grounded.

The runtime side stopped treating completion as a vague end state and started handling return-state transitions with more discipline. That makes Guardian less likely to blur together terminal, completed, and still-in-flight results. In practice, that is the difference between a system that looks finished and one that actually tracks completion honestly.

